body:
I tried this code: [playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=bfe131f8a2ac0cf1c27ed52edf58870c)

```rust
use std::marker::PhantomData;

trait Storable: Sized + Copy + Sync + Send + 'static{}

impl <T> Storable for T where T: Sized + Copy + Sync + Send + 'static{}

trait QueryProxyTrait{
    type Associated: Storable;
    fn get_item_pointers()->Self::Associated;
}

// This is struct with associated item
struct RefMutProxy<T: Storable>(PhantomData<T>);

impl<TR0: Storable> QueryProxyTrait for (RefMutProxy<TR0>,) {
    type Associated = i32;
    fn get_item_pointers()->Self::Associated{
        0i32
    }
}

// This is struct which impl fails to compile
struct Q<T: QueryProxyTrait>(PhantomData<T>);

impl<T> Q<(RefMutProxy<T>,)>
where T: Storable,
    // If line below is removed, it compiles
    (RefMutProxy<T>,): QueryProxyTrait
{
    fn get_data(){
        let v: <(RefMutProxy<T>,) as QueryProxyTrait>::Associated =
            <(RefMutProxy<T>,) as QueryProxyTrait>::get_item_pointers();
        // Here it fails to prove that v is i32
        let v: i32 = v;
    }
}
```

I expected to see this happen: Code compiles

Instead, this happened: compiler prints this error:
```
error[E0308]: mismatched types
  --> src/lib.rs:32:22
   |
32 |         let v: i32 = v;
   |                ---   ^ expected `i32`, found associated type
   |                |
   |                expected due to this
   |
   = note:         expected type `i32`
           found associated type `<(RefMutProxy<T>,) as QueryProxyTrait>::Associated`
   = help: consider constraining the associated type `<(RefMutProxy<T>,) as QueryProxyTrait>::Associated` to `i32`
   = note: for more information, visit https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch19-03-advanced-traits.html

```

### Meta
<!--
Bug occurs in beta and nightly too.
-->

`rustc --version --verbose`:
```
rustc 1.48.0 (7eac88abb 2020-11-16)
binary: rustc
commit-hash: 7eac88abb2e57e752f3302f02be5f3ce3d7adfb4
commit-date: 2020-11-16
host: x86_64-pc-windows-msvc
release: 1.48.0
LLVM version: 11.0
```

**P.S.**
If anyone faced same trouble, I solved it by removing this line in impl: `(RefMutProxy<T>,): QueryProxyTrait`

I found how to make this code compile (see comments in source) but I think rustc should either accept code above or print better error message.
